Description:
The DGU RGA IT OT Data & AI Mgmt is looking to recruit a Data Scientist.




EDP is a global energy group present in around 30 markets with a particular emphasis on renewable energies. With more than 45 years of experience, we have been consolidating a relevant presence on the world energy scene based on the commitment to be all-green by 2030, leading the energy transition. With more than 13,000 employees around the world, we are committed to using our energy and heart to drive a better tomorrow.




What you will do:

Analyse datasets from various renewable energy sources to identify trends, patterns, and insights for operational efficiency and decision-making;
Develop and implement predictive models to forecast equipment failures and maintenance needs, ensuring optimal performance and reliability of renewable assets;
Utilise advanced statistical and machine learning techniques to optimise the performance of renewable energy assets, including wind turbines, solar panels, and hydroelectric plants;
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate data from different sources, ensuring data quality and consistency;
Develop and optimise machine learning models using Python, including data transformation, feature engineering, and building data pipelines with Databricks and AzureML;
Support the deployment, monitoring, and troubleshooting of machine learning models.

Employment type: Full-Time

Work site: Hybrid Model

Work Place: Lisbon or Porto




What are we looking for:

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, Statistics or a related field or a related field;
Up to 3 years' professional experience in data scientist roles;
Good understanding of machine learning algorithms and concepts;
Good programming knowledge in Python and its math & machine learning packages such as numpy, scikit-learn, pandas, etc;
Familiarity with Azure and Databricks;
This role requires strong collaboration with various teams, including solution architects, development, operations, and business teams. Excellent communication skills are essential, as this role involves explaining complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

More than academic knowledge and technical skills, we are looking for ambitious people who are enthusiastic about the future and who bring human skills aligned with our purpose.




